/*
this is the bython script that allows me to create a voxel model from a polygon model
this script is not the best but it works

to make it work for yourself there is some conditions
you must fill all the data in the begining of the script
the input model:
    - is an obj
    - all color is from a single texture
    - texture alpha will be ignored (avoid transparent texture)
    - no materials

to create a texture that contains all the colors from a model with multiples
textures and also lighting information, I recomend baking the all model
to a texture in blender and then use this texture as the texture for the model

to use the output image of the model in shadertoy, follow this shader that explain how
to import custom textures: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lsGGDd

